HEADWORD: collapsible
<hw>collapsible</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Capable of collapsing or being
collapsed; <as>as, a <ex>collapsible</ex> boat</as>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>telescopic</stype>; <stype>tip-up</stype>] <see>Also See:
<er>folded</er>.</see> Antonym: <ant>noncollapsible</ant>.⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> collapsable.</syn>⟦br⟧
